-- Foxconn Plans $5 Billion Chengdu Production Base, Metropolis Daily Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-06T07:54:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/foxconn-plans-5-billion-chengdu-production-base-metropolis-daily-reports.html

          
          
             Foxconn Technology Co. plans to hire
100,000 people for its Chengdu production base, in which the
original equipment manufacturer will invest $5 billion, the West
China Metropolis Daily reported today, citing an agreement
bewteen Foxconn and the local government.  
 Foxconn has started to hire 1,000 people in Chengdu, at a
minimum monthly salary of 1,590 yuan, the Chengdu-based
newspaper said.  
